{\b #{\footnote html_intro.htm_mptintl}International Versions}\sa240\par\pard\plain
Modplug Tracker is written with a default page code of 0409 (English - US)\line
You can freely edit the resources to make a localized version of Modplug Tracker, 
although some strings are hardcoded in the code (not as resources).\line
I am trying to improve the support for easier localization, but it is a lot of work.\line
However, starting from v1.15.0154, MPT supports localized strings in the file MPT_INTL.INI\line
This file contains string sections for a specific language id. For example, in Australia, MPT will 
look for strings in the [Strings.0C09] (0C09=Australian English language id). If it isn't found, then it 
will look in the [Strings.0009] section (generic english), if not found, it will look in the 
[Strings] section (no language id), and if still not found, it will use the default value for the string.\line
For example, to set the option names in the setup general tab, the strings would be\line
{\i Setup.Gen.Opt1.Name=Play new notes while recording}\line
{\i Setup.Gen.Opt1.Desc=When this option is enabled, notes entered in the pattern editor will always be played (If not checked, notes won't be played in record mode).}\line
Feel free to email me if you have specific questions about this.\line
\line
\sa240\par\pard\plain
