{\b #{\footnote html_intro.htm_features}Tracker Features}\sa240\par\pard\plain
- Up to 64 channels supported for editing (up to 200 virtual channels)\line
- The following formats are supported for import:\line
- *.669: UNIS 669, 669 Composer modules.\line
- *.AMF: Asylum / DSMI modules.\line
- *.AMS: Velvet Studio AMS 1.x modules.\line
- *.DBM: DigiBooster Pro modules.\line
- *.DMF: X-Tracker modules.\line
- *.DSM: DSIK modules.\line
- *.FAR: Farandole Composer modules.\line
- *.IT:  Impulse Tracker modules.\line
- *.MDL: DigiTracker 1.x modules.\line
- *.MED: OctaMed modules (buggy).\line
- *.MID: Midi Files.\line
- *.MOD: ProTracker modules (4-32 channels, 15/31 samples).\line
- *.MTM: MultiTracker modules.\line
- *.NST: NoiseTracker modules.\line
- *.OKT: Oktalyzer Modules.\line
- *.PTM: PolyTracker modules.\line
- *.S3M: ScreamTracker III modules.\line
- *.STM: ScreamTracker II modules.\line
- *.ULT: UltraTracker modules (buggy).\line
- *.UMX: Musics from Unreal and Unreal Tournament\line
- *.WOW: Grave Composer modules.\line
- *.XM:  FastTracker II modules.\line
- All the above when zipped (*.MDZ, *.S3Z, *.XMZ, *.ITZ, *.ZIP).\line
\line
- ModPlug Tracker can save in the following formats:\line
- IT:  Impulse Tracker modules.\line
- MOD: ProTracker modules (4-32 channels, 15/31 samples).\line
- S3M: ScreamTracker III modules.\line
- XM:  FastTracker II modules.\line
- WAV: Wave Files (Direct-to-disk recording 8/16/32-bit, mono/stereo/quad)\line
\line
- There is two display modes, to respect FT2/IT notation: MOD/XM (commands 
  are displayed from 0 to X) and S3M/IT (commands are displayed from A to Z)\line
- You can edit multiple songs at the same time.\line
- The following sample formats are supported in the current version:\line
- *.WAV: Uncompressed Windows Wave File (PCM 8/16bit, mono/stereo).\line
- *.XI: Samples from XI instruments.\line
- *.PAT: UltraSound GF1 Patches (8/16-bit mono)\line
- *.S3I/*.SMP: ScreamTracker 3 / DigiTracker Samples\line
- *.ITS: Impulse Tracker Samples\line
- *.RAW: Support for importing any file as RAW sample data.\line
- *.AIF/*.AIFF/*.8SVX/*.8SV: Apple AIFF and 8SVX Audio Files\line
- Modplug Tracker also supports the following sound banks formats:\line
- *.DLS: Downloadable Sounds Banks\line
- *.SF2: SoundFont 2.0 Sound Banks\line
- FastTracker II XI and Impulse Tracker ITI instruments are supported for 
  import/export.\line
- Copy/Paste between different songs. It also allows you to use a windows-based 
  sample editor, and paste the samples directly into your song.\line
\line
